President Obama expresses his condolences to the families and loved ones of American soldiers who were killed in Afghanistan. He acknowledges the sacrifices made by the military and their families, and vows to continue working towards securing the country and upholding the values they believed in. The President also mourns the Afghan casualties who were striving for a better future for their country. He emphasizes the unity of all Americans in supporting the men and women in uniform who protect their freedom and security.